%% Data Flow Diagram - ODH Notebook Controller (kubeflow)
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6

sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User / Dashboard
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Webhook as NotebookWebhook<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant ImageReg as OpenShift Image Registry<br/>5000/TCP HTTPS
    participant Controller as OpenshiftNotebookReconciler
    participant OAuthSvr as OpenShift OAuth Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant ServiceCA as OpenShift Service CA

    Note over User,ServiceCA: Flow 1: Notebook Creation with OAuth

    User->>K8sAPI: POST Notebook CR<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: POST /mutate-notebook-v1<br/>Auth: API server mTLS
    Webhook->>K8sAPI: GET ImageStream tags<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
    K8sAPI-->>Webhook: ImageStream dockerImageReference
    Note over Webhook: Injects: OAuth proxy sidecar,<br/>CA bundles, pipeline config,<br/>proxy env vars, image resolution
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Mutated Notebook CR
    K8sAPI-->>User: Notebook created

    K8sAPI->>Controller: Watch event: Notebook created
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Route (TLS reencrypt)<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create {notebook}-tls Service<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create ServiceAccount<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create OAuthClient (cluster-scoped)<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create OAuth Secrets<br/>(cookie + client secret)
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create NetworkPolicies<br/>(ctrl-np + oauth-np)
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create CA ConfigMap<br/>(workbench-trusted-ca-bundle)

    Note over User,ServiceCA: Flow 2: User Accessing Notebook via OAuth Route

    participant Browser as User Browser
    participant Router as OpenShift Router<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant OAuthProxy as OAuth Proxy Sidecar<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant Notebook as Notebook Container<br/>8888/TCP HTTP

    Browser->>Router: GET https://{route-host}<br/>TLS (edge/reencrypt)
    Router->>OAuthProxy: Forward request<br/>TLS reencrypt
    OAuthProxy-->>Browser: 302 Redirect to OAuth Server
    Browser->>OAuthSvr: OAuth login<br/>HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    OAuthSvr-->>Browser: 302 Redirect with auth code
    Browser->>OAuthProxy: GET with OAuth token (cookie)<br/>HTTPS TLS
    OAuthProxy->>K8sAPI: SubjectAccessReview check<br/>get notebooks.kubeflow.org/{name}
    K8sAPI-->>OAuthProxy: Allowed
    OAuthProxy->>Notebook: Proxy to localhost:8888<br/>HTTP (same pod, no encryption)
    Notebook-->>OAuthProxy: Response
    OAuthProxy-->>Router: HTTPS Response
    Router-->>Browser: HTTPS Response

    Note over User,ServiceCA: Flow 3: Elyra Pipeline Config Reconciliation

    Controller->>K8sAPI: GET Dashboard CR<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: Dashboard status.url
    Controller->>K8sAPI: GET DSPA CR<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: DSPA S3 endpoint, bucket info
    Controller->>K8sAPI: GET S3 credential Secret<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: S3 credentials
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create/Update ds-pipeline-config Secret<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
